    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> See how you translated the similar expression in 8:20. Alternate translation: [During his reign]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> See how you translated the similar expression in 1:3. Alternate translation: [came] or [invaded]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The author is speaking as if Jehoiakim had been away somewhere and **returned**. He means that he decided to become a vassal of Egypt once again and so stopped serving Nebuchadnezzar. If it would be helpful in your language, you could state the meaning plainly. Alternate translation: [Then he resumed his previous loyalty to Egypt]
