      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The plural form **treasuries** suggests that these terms represent the valuable items that were in the treasury of each building. If it would be helpful in your language, you could use an equivalent expression or plain language. Alternate translation: [all of the valuable items that were in the treasury of the house of Yahweh and the treasury of the house of the king]
